'''公正世界理论'''或'''公正世界[[谬误|谬误]]'''（{{lang-en|Just-World Theory/Hypothesis}}），亦稱'''公平世界假定'''，是[[認知偏誤|認知偏誤]]的一種。这个假说由美国心理学家Melvin Lerner所提出<ref name="LernerSimmonsObserver">{{cite journal |last=Lerner |first=M. |last2=Simmons |first2=C. H. |year=1966 |title=Observer’s Reaction to the ‘Innocent Victim’: Compassion or Rejection? |journal=Journal of Personality and Social Psychology |volume=4 |issue=2 |pages=203–210 |doi=10.1037/h0023562 |pmid=5969146 |url=http://web.mit.edu/curhan/www/docs/Articles/biases/4_J_Personality_Social_Psychology_203_(Lerner).pdf |access-date=2016-08-07 |archive-date=2020-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101020152/http://web.mit.edu/curhan/www/docs/Articles/biases/4_J_Personality_Social_Psychology_203_(Lerner).pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，相信的人假设了这个世界是[[正義|公平]][[公正|公正]]的，因此心理运作模式总是“[[業|善有善报，恶有恶报]]”，坏事不降临在好人身上（例：「可憐之人」必「有可恨之處」），所以若某人遭遇不幸事件，则他做了坏事，恶有恶报，反之亦然，但事實可能並非如此，因而犯上[[邏輯學|邏輯學]]上的[[非形式謬誤|非形式謬誤]]。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pansci.asia/archives/87359|title=每個人都是不理性的人？淺談常見的歸因謬誤，及其背後的意義|accessdate=2016-08-07|author=|date=2015-10-26|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher=[[PanSci_泛科學|PanSci 泛科學]]|pages=|language=|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022093413/https://pansci.asia/archives/87359|archivedate=2020-10-22|quote=|dead-url=no}}</ref>

这个谬误最常见的例子，就是[[指责受害人|指责受害人]]。例如：被强奸的受害人，被人认为是由于个人不够小心或穿着暴露所导致，而忘了加害人才是应该被谴责的。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gender.psc.ntu.edu.tw/Gender/page/page_03_2.php?cat_id=92&mag_id=61&mag_series=%B3%D0%A5Z%B8%B9%A1i%A4Q%A4T%A5H%AB%E1%A7%EF%BA%D9%A4k%BE%C7%BE%C7%BBx%A1j&type=article&art_id=472&Qry=0|title=大學生對強姦受害者的態度研究|accessdate=2016-08-07|author=陳皎眉、藍采風|date=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|year=|month=|format=|work=女學學誌|publisher=[[臺大|臺大]]婦女研究室|pages=|language=|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418230524/http://gender.psc.ntu.edu.tw/Gender/page/page_03_2.php?cat_id=92&mag_id=61&mag_series=%B3%D0%A5Z%B8%B9%A1i%A4Q%A4T%A5H%AB%E1%A7%EF%BA%D9%A4k%BE%C7%BE%C7%BBx%A1j&type=article&art_id=472&Qry=0|archivedate=2018-04-18|quote=|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==對行為與態度的影響==
===暴力===
===霸凌===
有鑑於其他對於公正世界理論的研究，研究人員預期說較為相信公正世界理論的人更可能會指責[[霸凌|霸凌]]受害者；然而，研究顯示，較為相信公正世界理論的人，在事實上比其他人有更強烈的反[[霸凌|霸凌]]傾向，<ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1348/000709909X479105 | pmid=19930790| title=The association between adolescents' beliefs in a just world and their attitudes to victims of bullying| journal=British Journal of Educational Psychology| volume=80| issue=2| pages=183–198| year=2010| last1=Fox| first1=Claire L.| last2=Elder| first2=Tracey.| last3=Gater| first3=Josephine| last4=Johnson| first4=Elizabeth| s2cid=33974893| url=https://semanticschola r.org/paper/3f6e30cf501a02993d86777c4046f1ae0f1541a3}}</ref>其他一些研究也發現說較為相信公正世界理論的人比較不會去欺負他人、成為霸凌加害者；<ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1027/1016-9040.13.4.248 |title = School Bullying|journal = European Psychologist|volume = 13|issue = 4|pages = 248–254|year = 2008|last1 = Correia|first1 = Isabel|last2 = Dalbert|first2 = Claudia|s2cid = 145567888|url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/1711694294eef21252ec6d5e3402a556cd25caea}}</ref>也就是說，越相信公正世界理論的人，越不會參與霸凌、欺負他人，也越不會指責霸凌受害者。

這些研究結果驗證了Lerner對於公正世界信念是行為管理的「合約」的理解；此外，研究顯示對公正世界理論的信仰，在學校環境中，對兒童與青少年的心理健康有保護作用，<ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/10615800902729242 |pmid = 19333798|title = Belief in a just world and well-being of bullies, victims and defenders: A study with Portuguese and Indian students|journal = Anxiety, Stress & Coping|volume = 22|issue = 5|pages = 497–508|year = 2009|last1 = Correia|first1 = Isabel|last2 = Kamble|first2 = Shanmukh V.|last3 = Dalbert|first3 = Claudia|s2cid = 205725655|url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/ca1d145496d3740b12fdba4f2b406a7bc173d5f6}}</ref>同樣的狀況也出現在一般大眾當中。

===生病===
===貧困===
研究人员通过公正世界假说的视角探讨了人们对贫困的反应。坚持公正世界理论者与指责穷人有强相关，而对公正世界信念较弱的人则主张贫穷是来自于外部原因，包括世界经济体系、战争和剥削。<ref>{{Cite journal|doi = 10.2224/sbp.1990.18.2.235|title = Lay Causal Perceptions of Third World Poverty and the Just World Theory'|journal = Social Behavior and Personality|volume = 18|issue = 2|pages = 235–238|year = 1990|last1 = Harper|first1 = David J.|last2 = Wagstaff|first2 = Graham F.|last3 = Newton|first3 = J. Tim|last4 = Harrison|first4 = Kevin R.|url = http://inesad.edu.bo/developmentroast/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Harper-1990-Poverty-Explanations.pdf|access-date = 2021-10-26|archive-date = 2021-02-25|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210225004002/http://inesad.edu.bo/developmentroast/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Harper-1990-Poverty-Explanations.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/00224545.1992.9712107 |title = The Just World and the Third World: British explanations for poverty abroad| url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-social-psychology_1992-12_132_6/page/783 |journal = The Journal of Social Psychology|volume = 132|issue = 6|pages = 783–785|year = 1992|last1 = Harper|first1 = David J.|last2 = Manasse|first2 = Paul R.}}</ref>

